{
  "name": "RPlog_A_Business_Proposition_on_Kichnar",
  "title": "A Business Proposition on Kichnar",
  "summary": "Aboard Kichnar Station's Blue Nebula Cantina, the smuggler Piper -- operating under the alias Elysia Jaxom -- approaches the bar's proprietor, Tormod Belafunte, to pitch a holographic combat-gaming machine she claims will draw crowds at no cost to him. Watching from a corner booth, casino magnate Talon Karrde and his associate Ariana send over a musical advertising datacard for their soon-to-open Keepon Casino, drawing Piper into their conversation. Recognizing a rival operator and a richer venue, Piper redirects her sales pitch toward Karrde, and a barbed but cordial three-way negotiation unfolds, shadowed by old tension between Piper and Ariana. By the end Karrde expresses genuine interest, invites Piper and her partner Tyler McBride to the casino's opening to demonstrate the device, and Ariana personally guarantees their security. The parties exchange handshakes and Piper departs, leaving the deal open but promising.",
